arts.ttl: Barcelona learn outcome of Osasuna appeal over ineligible player, but what happens now?
arts.sum: RFEF's competition committee dismiss Osasuna's appeal over the alleged ineligibility of Barcelona's Inigo Martinez for their La Liga meeting last month.

arts.ttl: Osasuna lose appeal of Barça player eligibility
arts.sum: Osasuna's claim that Barcelona fielded an ineligible lineup by playing Iñigo Martínez against them last month has been rejected by the Spanish Football Federation.

arts.ttl: Barcelona: Osasuna lose appeal claiming Inigo Martinez was ineligible for rescheduled LaLiga clash
arts.sum: The defender’s participation in the rescheduled fixture had been questioned after withdrawing from Spain duty through injury

arts.ttl: Osasuna appeal over Barcelona player dismissed
arts.sum: Osasuna's appeal over Barcelona defender Inigo Martinez's eligibility to play in a La Liga against them is dismissed by Royal Spanish Football Federation.

Osasuna are now winless in eight ahead of Sunday's welcome of Girona. That said, they have drawn their last two, and this weekend's game presents them with a great chance to get back to winning ways. ...

arts.ttl: Barcelona escape punishment after accusation of using ineligible player
arts.sum: Barcelona will not face punishment for fielding an ineligible player last month in their 3-0 win over Osasuna, after the Disciplinary Committee ruled in their favour. The case centred around an injury to Inigo Martinez. Before the March international break, Inigo Martinez was called up by Spain for their Nations League games.
